---
description: Repository conventions for miscSkills (language rules for skills/READMEs, pre-commit hygiene check)
alwaysApply: true
---

Follow the repository conventions defined in @CLAUDE.md. In particular:

- Write README.md files in Japanese; write skill prompt files (SKILL.md and
  everything under references/) in English. Skill *outputs* follow the
  language of the target documents.
- Each skill set lives in its own `YYYYMMDD_name/` subfolder.
- Skills follow the Agent Skills open standard (SKILL.md with `name` and
  `description` frontmatter only; supporting files under `scripts/`,
  `references/`, `assets/`) so they stay portable across Claude Code,
  GitHub Copilot, and Cursor. Each skill's README lists the install paths
  for all three agents. Never write a skill as a `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`
  file — that format is Cursor-only.
- Before finishing work or committing, run `git status` (including untracked
  files) and verify nothing unfit for GitHub is included: runtime/work
  outputs, dry-run or scratch files, secrets (.env, keys, tokens), test
  inputs containing personal or business data (docx/xlsx/pdf), editor-local
  state (Obsidian workspace.json, non-rules `.cursor/` files), large
  binaries. Add offenders to .gitignore or delete them, and report to the
  user what was excluded.
